                      Full Artwork @ 300 dpi (png) -> 89 Mb


Not sure how I came to think this was a double cd of Bob and Joan dueting but I did. It is essentially the first album, both self titled, of Bob Dylan (1962) and Joan Baez (1960) with bonus tracks making a total of 33. No duets. This was the disappointment for me. However the inside liner notes were interesting, even with a couple of typos, and I came to appreciate the double album more. Of the two albums disc 2 featuring Joan Baez has worn the best but both albums are good and hold up well more than 50 years later. Just don't expect any duets or where the two appear on a single song together. There is of course Bob Dylan Live 1964 (Bootleg Series 6) where the two appear in concert for four songs. A promoter's dream not happening somehow....
